<br>
just because communications have come a long way doesn't change or make light of our living conditions either so please don't try to take away from that and make it out like we have a cushie situation because we can IM our loved ones, k?  that softens the blow but it doesn't change anything.<br>
<br>
i won't outline what it's like here for you.  you can say &quot;back when i was in desert storm&quot; all day long but here's the reality:  there are &quot;old timers&quot; in my unit who were also in desert storm, with this unit.  they will tell you the same as i will, and you should know even through vicarious media thrills,  this is not the same thing.  it is not the same timeline.  it is damn sure not the same situation.  <br>
<br>
yes.  telecommunications have come a long way in 12 years but...we all know that.  they have come a long way in the US as well.  I know when desert storm was going on i didn't even have the internet in my home...i didn't even know what it was and well most americans didnt even have a computer in their home.<br>
